Day 1

CHAT ETIQUETTE

Avoid too many messages
Send a single message

Why ?
Avoid spamming
Avoid miscommunication
Avoid missing of information

Parts of chat:
Opening - Greeting + Purpose + Introduction(only when you are writing to someone for the first time)
Probing - [Probe = get into details] ; You do this by questioning
    2 types of questioning:
        a. Open ended - Leaving the other person to share whatever they want
            Ex: Introduce yourself..
        b. Close ended - To the point info, one word answers, yes/no ans
            Ex: What is your name?
Acknowledgements - When others asked you for some info then acknowledge them like i'll send by EOD etc
        We can use reactions as acknowledgents but not to leaders and clients
Closing - Summarize + conformation
    Not summarize the entire chat -> Pickup only the important points
    Conformation -> before you closing, ask the other person if they have anything else to ask

You can use abrivation that are commonly used like EOD, ASAP, etc
    Avoid using them with people in leadership position and clients

