Day 2

CONFERENCE CALL

    Before the call -> During the call -> After the call

    1. Purpose
    2. Confirm list of participants
    3. Prepare agenda
    4. Schedule the meeting
    5. Send invites
    6. Role alllocation

    Structure of the meeting:
        1. Greetings (Introduction in some cases) (Or small talks before the call) 
        2. Roll call
        3. Agenda
        4. Discussion
        5. Sumarizing
        6. Close the call - schedule next meeting / reiterate very imp points / clarify questions

    Reactions -> Instant reply powered by emotions
    Responses -> well thought answers (even by thinking about the consequences)

    Skills required
        . Active listening: listen -> comprehend -> clarify -> respond
        . Paraphrasing - reiterate and get conformation
        . Questioning - 
            5Ws & 1H 
            5Ws -> Who, when, what, why, Where
            1H  -> How (tone)
    
    Situation handling:
    Handling Escalation calls:
        1. Attitude - calm, composed, positive
        2. Acknowledge - ack the issue
        3. Agreement - give sols to the client and the client chooses
        4. Action - initiating the process / give action plan
    
    After the call:
        1. MOM
        2. Send invites for next meeting

    Stand up call:
        Either in the morning / evening
        <= 15min

